<plot>"Everything Works Out" is both a song featured prominently in the film THE FALLS and the theme of this making-of documentary. Despite working with a tiny budget in some grueling locations and under the worst of global circumstances (day 3 of location photography was September 11, 2001), the team behind THE FALLS managed to complete the film on time and on budget. Then during post-production new challenges arose as the team labored to create over 225 visual effects shots and the director struggled through the editing process - ultimately creating a final cut that scored well with test audiences and won acceptance into 5 film festivals. With distribution finally secured - four years after pre-production began - everything did, at last, work out.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?184544</url></doc>
